                  <handDesc>
                     <!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Hand a: fine, regular. Hand b: fine, regular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid scarlet, strong red).</seg>
                        <date>17th cent. (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">- The rubrication is executed in different tones of
                           red: vivid scarlet and strong red (see e.g., fols. 42rb, 50va).&#xD; -
                           Nomina sacra; four red lines on the incipit page (fol. 16r: 2 lines
                           above, 2 lines below); incipits of some sections; the word täfäśśǝḥi
                           "rejoice"; elements of the punctuation signs; short chains of black and
                           red dots separating paragraphs executed by "hand b" (fols. 98vab, 99va);
                           nine dot asterisks are decorated at the right side with two red lines in
                           a forked shape, executed by "hand b" (e.g. 104vab); elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: <locus from="1r" to="97v">1r-97v</locus>; a fine, regular script with very small, wide and broadly
                        spaced
                        letters.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Hand b: <locus from="98ra" to="111vb">98ra-111vb</locus>, a fine script with slender
                        letters.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
